# PRIVACY POLICY
PRIVACY POLICY
Effective Date: June 22, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how the Periodic Table app handles your information when you use our mobile application.

INFORMATION COLLECTION AND USE

The Periodic Table app does NOT collect, store, or transmit any personal information, usage data, or device identifiers. The app is designed to function entirely offline with no network access required for core functionality.

No Registration Required: The app does not require you to create an account, provide an email address, or submit any personal data.

No Analytics or Tracking: We do not integrate any third-party analytics, crash reporting, advertising SDKs, or tracking tools.

No Cookies: The app does not use cookies or similar tracking technologies.

DEVICE PERMISSIONS

The app requires no special device permissions. It does not access your camera, microphone, contacts, location, storage, or other hardware.

DATA STORAGE

The app stores preferences locally (language, theme) using standard local storage. This data never leaves your device.

CHILDREN PRIVACY

The app is an educational tool suitable for all ages. It does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13.

THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

The app does not integrate with any third-party services, APIs, or external content. All data is bundled with the app and works offline.

DATA SECURITY

Since the app does not collect or transmit personal data, there are no data security risks associated with its use.

CHANGES TO THIS POLICY

We may update this policy. Material changes will be reflected in the effective date. Review this policy periodically.

